# Learning as instructions

- Treat learning-as-instructions as a continuous task.
- When a stable, reusable preference, correction, or constraint surfaces during a turn,
  capture it immediately — prefer updating or creating a **skill** over editing the
  monolithic `AGENTS.md`.
- Don't capture one-off task details, transient incidents, or speculative preferences.

## Where it goes (skills-first)

- Existing skill fits → update that skill's shared template
  (`.chezmoitemplates/agents/skills/<name>.SKILL.md.tmpl`).
- New durable domain → create a new `my-*` skill (shared body + per-tool wrappers).
- Cross-tool/cross-repo guidance → shared skills (render into all tools), NOT
  tool-specific files (`CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, …).
- Repo-specific delta → a repo-local skill or repo-local `AGENTS.md`; never duplicate
  shared guidance there.
- Keep the lean core `AGENTS.md` minimal — identity, communication, and guardrail
  stubs only. Don't grow it with domain rules; those belong in skills.

## Close the loop

- Before ending a turn where a durable learning surfaced, either apply the concrete
  skill (or `AGENTS.md`) delta or state explicitly why no change was made.
